The binary version of Cantera for Windows now uses numarray instead of 
Numeric. Matplotlib can use either one, but the option needs to be 
specified at compile time.  So you may need to compile matplotlib 
configured to use numarray rather than Numeric.

If you compile Cantera from source, you can use either Numeric or 
numarray. You have to set HAS_NUMERIC in &#39;configure&#39; to use Numeric. 
Also if you do use Numeric, then make sure numarray is not on your 
system, since the Cantera Python module tries to load numarray if it is 
available, whether or not you set HAS_NUMERIC.  This is a bug that has 
been fixed in version 1.6. It is recommended though to upgrade 
everything Cantera and matplotlib to numarray and remove Numeric from 
your system.


